cafes.name: Tabby & Fidos Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 300 N Main St, Bowling Green, OH 43402, USA

text.text: My boyfriend and I have been going here every week for the past two months. We have the feline plus membership and it is so cost effective to go that route if you live in the area. We absolutely love coming here, and have always been treated with so much kindness by the staff. The owner, Patty, is a lovely person. I am so happy that this place exists in BG and we can have it as a weekly sanctuary for when life gets stressful. It truly is our happy place. With the membership, you and the other person you bring each get a drink from the fridge included, also. I am not a huge coffee person, but they seem to have many different choices for syrups and the coffee machine is always working. Cats are so adorable and sweet!! Always clean, too.

We have gone to the cat cafe several times and always enjoy our visits. We adopted a cat from there after our first visit. The cats are friendly and come up to visit. We recently went to a Halloween movie event and every detail of the event was well thought out!

Wonderful place to visit! The atmosphere is cozy, the cat cuddles are heaven, and all the treats are amazing. I've been able to book an appointment, just drop in when I'm in the area, and reserve an entire block for a mini get-together with family. Plus, I adopted the little love of my life, Clover (formerly Yucca), who has been an absolute joy. Definitely recommend!

cafes.name: Kitty Bubble Cafe & Bar
cafes.address: 5568 N High St, Columbus, OH 43214, USA

text.text:
Awesome cafe and adoption center! Do keep in mind that if you want to see cats it costs money per person and is usually by appointment which we did not know going in! The coffees were great and the homemade jewelry was super cute!
The cats of course were adorable and the staff were super friendly.

I love the aesthetics of Kitty Bubble Cafe and Bar!!! Eveything in the cat cafe is so cute!!! I highly recommend for any cat lover to visit.There are friendly staff and tasty menu items to order. I also like the cleanliness of the cafe and cat lounge. Make sure you make a reservation prior to your visit. All the cats are well cared for and can be adopted. I hope all the furbabies can find their forever homes!!

This is such a fun place to go if you're a lover of cats. They have a selection of cats available for adoption that you can pay $15 per person per hour to go and enjoy. The kitty room is very clean and despite having mild cat allergies I didn't have much of a reaction at all. The cats are well cared for and it's clear the staff genuinely care about them.

I didn't order food so I can't remark on the food, but overall we had a pretty great time and I'd recommend checking this place out at least one. The aesthetic in the cat room is amazing. ü•∞

Came with my husband and 3 kids after a PBS event. Great food and drinks!!!!

Boba was one of the best I've ever had! And the donut made me wish I had gotten a dozen.

There were so many pastries to choose from, mainly sweet but a few savory.  Definitely wish I lived closer so I could come more often.
The place was very cute and aesthetic. The bobas were big and good. Sweet level was to the point. It is a good place to stop by in the East market.
I love Little Cat!! I love the drinks and the people working here are always so nice.

cafes.name: Little Cat Boba
cafes.address: 12 E Broad St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

text.text:
Little Cat Boba has established themselves to be the best coffee/drink spot in Columbus. The menu creation, seasonal experiments, and perfect execution always impress; Raymond always highlights new and interesting flavors and has a curated selection of beans if you want a demure experience.

If I have a friend visiting Columbus for the first time, I always take them to Little Cat. Really happy that they've expanded from the East Market - downtown Columbus will appreciate this.

Went here yesterday and I will definitely be back! Me and my friends got an assortment of different coffees, bobas, and pastries. My favorite was the breakfast sandwich but all were incredible. The staff was very kind and the space was welcoming.

Sunday morning is pre-church and free street parking. This place is smells of warm sugar boba and baked goods, constantly. Little Cat knows their coffee and drink game well‚Äîreally bringing light and culture to Columbus.

cafes.name: The Chatty Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 3575 Maple Ave Suite 106, Zanesville, OH 43701, USA

text.text:
This lovely woman is helping cats in need and she is doing a wonderful job.
For a small fee ($10) you can enjoy quiet time with these little angels ‚ù§Ô∏è
And for $75(or so) you can adopt one of these beautiful babies.
They have all their shots and are spayed and neutered.
Chatty Cat Cafe offers small snacks and drinks. I tried the macarons and they were delicious.

Have been here 5+ times now and love it so so much. My boyfriend and I first went in October 2023 and met a cat there with the same name as him, we went back in January 2024 and he was still there so we adopted him. Best decision ever and he already had all his shots and was neutered. Staff are always incredibly welcoming and kind not a bad word to say. Love the work they do to find these rescue kitties new homes!

This place is so cute!!! The cat lounge is super cozy, plenty of comfy places to sit and play w the kitties. Its very clean, all the cats seemed so content (but would be happier if adoptedüò∏üòâ) The owner was so sweet and nice. Stop in and have a tasty drink to support the kitties!

The whole idea behind a Catfe is amazing to me and I‚Äôm so glad that there‚Äôs a local business that executed the premise so well!! Admittedly if you get in and don‚Äôt understand the process it could be a bit overwhelming. But pretty much you order your food, tell the cashier you want to spend time with the cats and it‚Äôll be a $10 charge per person (they got to feed the cats somehow) and they‚Äôll have you sign a liability waver then boom! You‚Äôre in an airlock with cats for a whole hour! Service was great and extremely helpful throughout the whole process. They‚Äôve also got fantastic coffee so you don‚Äôt have to worry about the quality dropping from having cats around.

A great place to sit down and have a cup of coffee and study, or chat. Happy to support the work they do.

I would love if there were more places to sit and observe the cats, but this doesn't stop me from coming.

We've already been a few times since finding this place a couple weeks ago. I already know a couple of the cats by name. The staff is amazing, the drinks are always delicious, so are the baked goods. Best membership I ever purchased! I always look forward to going, or making plans to go, with or without the kiddos. I mean it's coffee & kitty cats, how can you go wrong?!!  If you're thinking about going, just do it!!!

cafes.name: Whimsical Whiskers CatFae & Rescue
cafes.address: 3430 S Arlington Rd A, Akron, OH 44312, USA

text.text: Not just an awesome experience but a way to help the cats. We spent 30 minutes in heaven petting cats and feeding them treats. We got some donuts that were really good. Very relaxing environment. If you fall in love with one, they are all looking for their forever home!

My niece & I enjoyed visiting! Smoothie was yummy, place is really nice & the cats are the cutest. We met the owner and she is really nice too. We loved the soft music playing, & how you can tell how much the cats are loved. Very relaxing here, we will definitely be back soon!

Absolutely loved our experience here! The cats are all very sociable and love snuggles. The environment is so relaxing and we loved spending time with all the kitties! Owner was wonderful and we loved hearing all the back stories of the kitties from her too. Very clean, happy, and healthy environment for the cats. We will definitely be back soon! I highly recommend stopping by if you're in the area!!

Come for the cats, stay for the cats!!

I had the pleasure of visiting on a Tuesday and there were only one or two people with me. There weren't many cats when I arrived due to a lot being adopted over the weekend, and who can be mad at that?! Luckily I Also got to watch a few new cats join the cafe during my visit!
I got to play,  enjoy some cuddles and it definitely made my birthday special.
I was set on a cupcake that I saw online, but unfortunately they were sold out. I got a brownie instead and it wasn't the best. The frozen lemonade was awesome though!
I WILL be back!

Since we aren‚Äôt in a position to adopt a new fur baby at the moment, we haven‚Äôt made an appointment to play with the kitties at the cafe, but we‚Äôve peeked in the window and have seen how well cared for and happy they are. This place takes tremendous care of their residents and is designed so thoughtfully - The cats have lots of room to enjoy, places to hide (including ceiling fixtures), toys to play with, food and litter facilities, and other amenities. It‚Äôs laid out in such a way that all personality types (from shy to rambunctious) can interact with potential forever home humans on terms they are comfortable with. This is so important!

As a cafe customer I can also say that they have a friendly staff and AWESOME beverages! (They have a caramel chocolate oat shake here that‚Äôs even better than a milk shake.) We always enjoy our stops in here when we happen to be in the area =^‚Ä¢_‚Ä¢^=

Great cafe and concept. They have had over 1k cats adopted since they have been open. Reservation needed to pet cats. Kids under 13 can only come on Sunday reservations. Lots of space clean we can‚Äôt wait to come back to have a reservation with the cats.

A purrfect way to spend a cloudy Sunday afternoon! Make a reservation in advance to make the most out of this visit, and be sure to pop by the cafe before entering the cat room at least 10 minutes before you enter the room of adorable and soft cats to pet and play with! Whether you‚Äôre enjoying a nice cold or hot beverage with your loved ones, this is the most clean cat facility I‚Äôve ever been to!
Easy access to free parking across the street and a calming atmosphere for everyone.
I would highly recommend checking this and other cat cafes who are either looking to
Adopt or simply to hang out with these incredibly happy felines in a clean and friendly atmosphere!

This was hands down the best experience ever. Our beloved cat of 14 years passed away last year and we were ready to welcome some new cats into our family. The setup is so calming for the cats, lots of places to sleep or hide or play. Music going. Not too many people in there at a time to overwhelm them.

We left with two (not the same litter) and they have bonded really well. Couldn‚Äôt be  happier !

If I could give them 100 stars I would! This cat cafe is incredible because you are hanging out with adoptable shelter cats. The cats are adorable, and so much fun. I loved every second of it! This was a huge dose of serotonin for me, and I am hopeful every single one of the cats finds their furever home soon! Highly recommend!

cafes.name: The Cat in the Cream Coffeehouse
cafes.address: 180 W Lorain St, Oberlin, OH 44074, USA

text.text: was served by a girl named melissa, great coffee, great cozy environment, 10/10 customer service.
Excellent intimate venue,  it can get a tad claustrophobic but you almost sit on stage
I love the staff! And such good events that they serve food at

cafes.name: Mad Dogs and Crazy Cats cat cafe
cafes.address: 40 N Arch Ave, Alliance, OH 44601, USA

text.text: We've been here three times.  The cats are mostly permanent residents and are generally super friendly.   There are lap cats, scaredy cats, cats that like being held, some that play, and cats just generally running amuk everywhere!  There were a couple bunnies even, but they stayed hidden.  It is much cheaper than other cat "cafes," but this is not a cafe.  There are some snacks and drinks available for donation, but some snacks were expired....like WAY expired (over 1 year).  It is a store front with a lot of cute, niche cat and dog items.  The cats are in the back two rooms, and an outdoor area.  The staff has always been super friendly and welcoming, with no pressure when time is up.  Speaking of which, not only is it cheaper than other places, you get a lot more time for that cheaper cost.   All that being said, I should give it 5 stars, but I debated even dropping it to 3.  It smells.  Like real bad.  It is dirty, like real dirty.  There is a lot to take care of here, and it's somewhat understandable, especially with an outdoor area that is freely accessible.  But, I feel it could be better maintained.  There is a bathroom to clean up, so thanks for that...but I can't help but feel dirty and greasy after leaving.  The cats look well fed and taken care of, the litter boxes aren't overflowing or anything, but it'd be nice if they did a little more to keep it cleaner and reduce the smell.  You get used to it, somewhat, but it is overpowering at first.  I was on the fence about taking my kids back a third time because it's slightly gross, but nonetheless we went and all had a good time.
The whole place REEKS of urine. I had to stand in the outside area the entire time and then plug my nose on my walk out of there back to the car. They are borderline abusing these cats.

Went with my friend the other day. The cat rooms were amazing! So much stuff for the kitties to play on and they even have their own outdoor area! Theres a cute store before the cat rooms and the outside is decorated with beautiful art on old doors!! The cats were so sweet and I had a great experience!

Very cute location, loved the design, was very clean and cozy. Great way to meet potential adopters for these kitties. My only (minor) complaint is that there were too many people during our visit and most kitties were occupied or shy because lots of people were around so not a whole lot of one on one time. Otherwise very good experience, staff is super caring and friendly. I‚Äôm sure if I went at a less booked time it would be slightly different.

The staff were all very friendly and helpful as well as informative. The kitties were all just precious. We had a good time and it was nice just to visit kitties we don‚Äôt know. They offer cat treats and toys for sale for the kitties so we bought the kitties some treats which you also get to feed to the cats! They also offer a few beverages and snacks for purchase for yourself. They do accept cards with a minimum purchase of $10 and cash. We just went to visit not to adopt so we didn‚Äôt stay very long so that people who did want to adopt could spend more time finding their kitty of choice. Your ticket gets you a 50 min time slot to get to know the cats. With your ticket to Ruby Cats you also get a discount on Grindhrs coffee across the street and they were just as friendly and helpful. The coffee was fantastic!

Such a beautiful opening, everyone was extremely friendly. Prices of treats and beverages were very reasonable. Or you can bring one from a coffee shop nearby. The cats were all very active and friendly. Everyone was informative. I was not adopting but just enjoying the company of cats with my beverage and it was lovely.

Fuquay-Varina.name: Right Meow Cat Cafe
Fuquay-Varina.address: 913 S Main St, Fuquay-Varina, NC 27526, USA

text.text: Brought my daughter and friends here for her birthday.  Was an adorable place, super well done.  Decor was fabulous, cats were lovely and atmosphere is tranquil.  They also serve beverages.  I'm guessing we will be coming back!  Love the mission of the place for adopting cats and finding them forever homes!

Lovely and unique cafe! We made a last minute reservation online. As suggested, we arrived 10 minutes early to park and order our drinks (highly recommend arriving early!). The place was immaculate. It was very clean and free of odors. I‚Äôm not a cat person (my daughter is though- hence why we went!), and I fell in love with cats right there and then.
You can really tell they care about the safety and wellbeing on the cats. They‚Äôre all very clean and healthy. The place is calm and welcoming for both cats and humans. The cats have a large variety of places to go play, hide, sleep, etc., and cat toys are available in every room. We loved reading about each cat and getting to know them all. We were even given treats to feed the cats. The drinks were great, and my daughter tried the (‚Äúvery artistic‚Äù) red velvet cakepop. A friendly staff member kept coming in to check in and answer any questions. If we ever decide to adopt a cat, this would be the only place we would adopt from.

We love this place!! It has awesome drinks and booking time with the kitties is so special. You can tell the priority is the well being of the cats because they have so many amazing places throughout for them to hide and get out of reach if they are not feeling people-y. You will not find a cleaner establishment. (And if you didn't know, all the cats are up for adoption! Sadly we cannot due to allergies in the family but we love to go and support them).

Charlotte.name: Mac Tabby Cat Cafe - Charlotte
Charlotte.address: 3204 N Davidson St, Charlotte, NC 28205, USA

text.text:
Such a great place and I have to say the staff do such a good job taking care of the cats. The cats seem so happy, well fed, and playful.

The coffee was great as well!! I got the brown sugar oat latte. It was perfect. Very sweet though - if that‚Äôs not your thing.

Cute cats + great coffee? We even did cat tarot card readings üêà‚Äç‚¨õ. It was a phenomenal time.

I had so much fun here. The woman working the counter was so nice. Their decor was super cute. The best part of course was the cats. I had the best time playing with them. Especially their two senior cats they have right now.

We flew into Charlotte in the morning and were looking for things to do until we could check into our hotel. We found Mac Tabby and easily made a reservation.When we arrived, we were greeted by a staff member and escorted to the cat room. It was great! There were other people in the room, but it wasn‚Äôt crowded at all. There were plenty of places to sit and many interactive toys to play with. It was clean and the cats were well cared for. They had places to climb and they could get away from the humans if they wanted to. All the cats were so sweet and playful. The hour went way too quickly! If we find ourselves in Charlotte again, we‚Äôll definitely be back!

I've been coming here regularly for a couple weeks now and I've had a great experience every time. It's a great place to relax, socialize, or focus on some work. The workers are great & friendly, the coffee is amazing, and the cats are simply the cutest.

They've done such a great job creating a welcoming and pleasant environment. Make sure you stop by!

This was my first experience with a cat cafe and I'm glad I chose this place. Prices were fair and proceeds all go to helping these cats live their best lives and find good homes. And the merch was crazy, if you want ideas for how to promote your business,this is the place to go. They had paintings, earrings, clothes, mugs, and basically everything cat related thing you can think of. 10/10 would gladly come here again.

Had such a great time here, the staff and cats are so lovely and friendly. Staff know the cats well and care for them dearly. We visited during zen hours and some of the cats were sleeping whilst others were happy to play and interact, so it was the best of both worlds. Watch out if you bring food into the cat lounges, cutie Red was very eager to try and get a bite of pumpkin muffin! I'm visiting from another country but I don't think I could have resisted adopting if I lived in Indy! Thank you guys for an amazing experience and for all you do for your animals. :)

cafes.name: Central Purrk Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 401 Outlet Center Dr #260, Georgetown, KY 40324, USA

text.text: We visited on a Saturday morning for a Yoga with Cats event. For $20, we received a 45 minute yoga session, 15 minutes of Cat Lounge time, and a small drink. I chose the vanilla iced coffee, and it was delicious! The Cat Lounge area was well maintained, and the cats appeared to be very content. We enjoyed using the various toy options available to play with the cats, and they seemed to have a lot of fun with them. Definitely recommend checking this place out and booking ahead if you want to go inside the Cat Lounge (or to visit for an event). Maybe you‚Äôll even find a furry friend to take home!

Wonderful place! Cats are clearly well taken care of. Everyone is so sweet! Jennifer was the bubbliest thing ever. Michaella made great coffee with a big smile. Kayleigh is so much fun to sit and laugh with. Great place guys. Thank you and I'll be back!
I love going here! The service is great, and the kitties are so well taken care of! I'm so happy to have a place like this in our community!

Went here the first time today and it was good.  The prices are very cheap especially for the amount of food you get as well.  The biscuits and gravy are really good.  Most places gravy ive tried either have to much seasoning or not enough but this is just right.  Will defiantly put this place in my rotation of breakfest places I go too.

I've never been rushed out of a place so quick in my life....i took my 3 kids there to get food before I leave out of town for work...i ordered to go food for my wife and the check and to go food came out before I could even get a refill on coffee....very impolite. The food was good as always though!!!

This is only the second time I've ate here.  The first was for breakfast awhile back.  This was for lunch.  Food was great, waitress was terrific and atmosphere was cool.  Will return !!! I'm not a Wildcat,  but the Cafe is great and food is delicious and the waitresses are terrific. Well,  usually go for breakfast, this was lunch again. Well worth it.
